<promed@promedmail.org>

[Japan's conclusion (item 2) that meat-and-bone meal (MBM) made from
cows (how many?) imported from Britain in 1982 and 1987 might have
caused the cases in local cattle, is not unrelated to the Canadian
situation. About 160 live bovines were imported from UK to Canada
during the years 1982 to 1990, at least 45 of them in the critical
period 1988/89. For further details and their fate -- including
recycling -- see posting 20030529.1311. - Mod.AS]
